com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.messaging.network

Class AbstractNetworkMessageSender

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.messaging.AbstractMessageSender
      • com.ibm.watson.dsm.platform.messaging.network.AbstractNetworkMessageSender
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMessageSender
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NetworkMessageSender

    public abstract class AbstractNetworkMessageSender
extends AbstractMessageSender
implements IMessageSender
    Defines most of the mechanisms to send a message to a receiver. Subclasses must implement toByteArray(IApplicationDescriptor, IMessage) to convert the instances of IApplicationDescriptor and IMessage into a byte array which is sent over the socket. A subclass of AbstractNetworkMessageReceiver defines AbstractNetworkMessageReceiver.getSourceAndMessage(InputStream) which parses the bytes that are sent, assuming the two subclasses are using in conjunction to send and receive messages.
    Author:
    dawood
